    Compose a Prior for a Time Main Effect or Interaction

    compose_time.Rd

    Create a composite prior for a time main effect, or for an interaction involving time. The composite prior always contains a trend, and may contain a cyclical effect, a seasonal effect, and an error.

    Usage

    compose_time(trend, cyclical = NULL, seasonal = NULL, error = NULL)

    Arguments

    trend

    Prior describing the long-run behavior of the series. See below for choices. Required.

    cyclical

    Prior describing departures from the long-run trend that do not have a fixed period. See below for choices. Optional.

    seasonal

    Prior describing departures from the long-run trend that have a fixed period. See below for choices. Optional.

    error

    Prior for additional idiosyncratic variation. See below for choices. Optional

    Value

    An object of class "bage_prior_compose"

    Details

    TermMain effectsInteractions
    trendLin(), RW(), RW2(), Sp()ELin()
    seasonalSeas()ESeas()
    cyclicalAR(), AR1()EAR(), EAR1()
    errorN()N()

    Examples

    compose_time(
  trend = Lin(),
  cyclical = AR()
)
